         <abstract>
            <p>This paper considers the nonlinear operator $T$, which acts on 4-dimensional vectors with nonnegative real components. $T$ transforms such a vector into a new vector whose components are the magnitudes of the differences of cyclically adjacent pairs of components of the previous vector. We show that $T$ is not nilpotent.</p>
